{
  "brand": "Optoma",
  "device": "PROJECTOR",
  "variant": "Optoma HD/W/X/EH/UHD/ZH/ZU series (ASCII protocol)",
  "controlType": "RS232",
  "notes": [
    "Source: Optoma RS232 & Telnet Command Codes (covers HD/W/X/EH/UHD series, W501/X501/EH501 reference doc).",
    "Wire: DB9 cross-over (null-modem). 9600 8N1, no flow control.",
    "Format: '~XX<cmd_id> <value><CR>' where cmd_id is 3 digits with leading zeros.",
    "Projector ID byte ('XX') is 00 for broadcast / single-projector setups; replace with 01-99 for daisy chain.",
    "Reply: 'P' (pass) or 'F' (fail), 100-300ms after send.",
    "Information request commands ('~XX12n 1') return ASCII strings prefixed 'OKddd' or similar: ~XX121 1 -> Input Source (00=None,01=Reserved,02=VGA1,03=VGA2,04=S-Video,05=Video,06=BNC,07=HDMI1,08=HDMI2,etc). ~XX122 1 -> Software Version. ~XX123 1 -> Display Mode. ~XX124 1 -> Power State (0=Off,1=On). ~XX125 1 -> Brightness. ~XX126 1 -> Contrast. ~XX150 1 -> System status: 'OKabbbbccdddde' (a=power,bbbb=lamp hours,cc=source,dddd=fw,e=display mode). ~XX151 1 -> Model name (1=X501/2=W501/3=EH501 etc.). ~XX108 1 -> Lamp hours."
  ],
